089/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-07-17","Teachers: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the wastage rate was of qualified teachers in the state-funded sector in (a) St Helens and (b) the North West in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Conor McGinn","St Helens North","Conor McGinn","165072"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943090","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-07-23","<p>We remain deeply concerned about the human rights situation in Xinjiang. We raised our concerns in the UK statement at the Human Rights Council in June 2018 and with the Chinese authorities at the last UK/China Human Rights Dialogue which took place in June 2017. My officials will continue to monitor the situation in Xinjiang closely.</p><p>​</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-07-23T11:11:25.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943090/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943090/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943090/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-07-17","China: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his Chinese counterpart on the human rights situation in Xinjiang.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","164913"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943091","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-07-24","<p>The UK fully harmonised with the EU Pet Travel Scheme requirements in 2012. Data regarding the number of dogs entering Great Britain under the scheme from 2012-2017 can be found below.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Dogs</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>139643</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>152075</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>155444</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>164836</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>275876</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017</p></td><td><p>287016</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-07-24T11:33:32.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943091/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943091/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943091/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-07-17","Dogs: Imports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many dogs have been imported into the UK via the Pet Travel Scheme in each year since its introduction.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","164961"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943092","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-07-24","<p>The UK fully harmonised with the requirements of the Balai Directive for dog movements in 2012. The data for dog imports under the Balai Directive from 2012 to 2017 can be found in the attached Annex.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This data was extracted from the Trade Control and Expert System (TRACES). In some cases imports are recorded on TRACES as ‘<em>Canis familiaris</em> / <em>Felis catus’</em>, so APHA is unable to distinguish between cat or dog imports. These are included in the table in the column ‘Mixed’.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-07-24T10:45:58.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943092/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943092/answer","PQ 164962 - Balai Directive.xlsx","PQ 164962 - Balai Directive.xlsx","Annex - PQ 164962 - Balai Directive","Annex - PQ 164962 - Balai Directive","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943092/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-07-17","Dogs: Imports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many dogs have been imported using the Balai Directive in each year since its introduction; and if he will publish the number of dogs imported from each country of origin for each of those same years.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","164962"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943093","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-07-23","<p>The UK, as a member of the UN Security Council, strongly condemned the recent violence in Haiti and called for all parties to remain calm and to exercise restraint. Following the resignation of the Prime Minister on 14 July, there is currently no government in Haiti. Our Ambassador will call on the new Foreign Minister, when he or she is appointed.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-07-23T16:27:43.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943093/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943093/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943093/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-07-17","Haiti: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with Haiti officials on the political situation in that country.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","164914"
