"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942536","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-07-19","<p>Mrs Zaghari-Ratcliffe was arrested on 3 April 2016 as she was returning to the UK from a family holiday in Iran. She was sentenced to five years in prison. In 2017, two appeals against her conviction were rejected. We will continue to take action on all our dual national cases in line with what we believe will produce the best outcomes in their cases.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-07-19T14:53:36.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942536/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942536/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942536/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-07-16","Nazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent update he has received on a potential release date for Nazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe.","false","Biography information for Christine Jardine","Edinburgh West","Christine Jardine","164523"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942537","Department for Transport","false","2018-07-20","<p>The information is not held in the format requested and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>The correspondence management system focusses on dealing with a wide range of transport issues; it does not focus specifically on categorising each piece of correspondence in this level of detail.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-07-20T09:33:27.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942537/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942537/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942537/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-07-16","Railways: Complaints","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many public complaints in respect of train delays his Department received in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","164499"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942538","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-20","<p>NHS England has been in intensive discussions with Vertex to encourage it to price Orkambi at a level that would allow NHS England to fund its use without adversely impacting other patients. I and the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Health (Lord O’Shaughnessy) have been keeping an extremely close eye on these discussions and wrote to Vertex in April, urging it to commit to pricing that is responsible and proportionate. I also re-iterated this message in the adjournment debate on 17 July, Official report, columns 383-4.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-07-20T10:09:26.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942538/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942538/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942538/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-16","Orkambi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care what plans he has to ensure his Department continues to engage and meet with NHS England and Vertex to discuss access to Orkambi.","false","Biography information for Luke Hall","Thornbury and Yate","Luke Hall","164468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942539","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-20","<p>It is a key commitment of this Government to ensure that people with comparatively rarer conditions, like cystic fibrosis, get the same quality, safety and efficacy in medicines as those who have more common conditions.</p><p> </p><p>However, it is also necessary that Vertex prices Orkambi fairly and responsibly. That is why we must go through the right process with Vertex and NHS England, not the Government, working together to secure the best outcome for patients. NHS England has been in intensive discussions with Vertex to encourage it to price Orkambi at a level that would allow NHS England to fund its use without adversely impacting other patients. I and the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Health (Lord O’Shaughnessy) have been keeping an extremely close eye on these discussions and wrote to Vertex in April, urging it to commit to pricing that is responsible and proportionate. I also re-iterated this message in the adjournment debate on 17 July, Official report, columns 383-4.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-07-20T10:10:54.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942539/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942539/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942539/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-16","Orkambi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether ensuring access to Orkambi for people with cystic fibrosis is a priority for his Department.","false","Biography information for Luke Hall","Thornbury and Yate","Luke Hall","164469"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942540","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-20","<p>We are informed by NHS England that at the last meeting on 4 July, it was agreed that both parties would take time to reflect before a further meeting was arranged. NHS England has subsequently made a substantially increased proposal to Vertex and has offered to meet to discuss and clarify any aspects as required by the company.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-07-20T09:48:08.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942540/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942540/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942540/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-16","Orkambi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether a date has been set for the next meeting between NHS England and Vertex to discuss access to the drug Orkambi.","false","Biography information for Luke Hall","Thornbury and Yate","Luke Hall","164470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942541","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-20","<p>It is not in the Department’s gift to impose any requirement upon Vertex to waive its confidentiality clause or to disclose details of any offer in the negotiations around National Health Service access to the drug Orkambi. However, Ministers at the department have publicly urged Vertex to consider the offer made by NHS England and to waive confidentiality so that we can all see, in the interests of transparency, the kind of prices it is seeking to charge the NHS.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-07-20T09:43:39.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942541/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942541/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942541/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-16","Orkambi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what his Department's policy is on Vertex (a) waiving its confidentiality clause on the negotiations around NHS access to the drug Orkambi and (b) disclosing details of its offer to NHS England.","false","Biography information for Luke Hall","Thornbury and Yate","Luke Hall","164471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942542","Department for Transport","false","2018-07-24","<p>Transport in London is devolved to the Mayor of London, and it is for him to consider what, if any, assessment is made of the impacts of congestion on the London taxi trade.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-07-24T11:28:30.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942542/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942542/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942542/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-07-16","Taxis: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he has made an assessment of the effect of increasing traffic congestion on the viability of the cab trade in London; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Paul Scully","Sutton and Cheam","Paul Scully","164456"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942543","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-19","<p>No specific assessment has been made. The Children’s Hospice Grant is awarded annually and administered by NHS England. During 2016/17, NHS England worked with Together for Short Lives, the leading children’s end of life care charity, on a consultation on allocation method for the grant in 2017/18. All children’s hospices were invited to participate in the consultation.</p><p> </p><p>Following the consultation, NHS England decided to maintain the grant funding at its then current level of £11 million per year for 2017/18 and 2018/19, and review the grant allocation again in 2019/20.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-07-19T11:25:46.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942543/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942543/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942543/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-16","Hospices: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the answer of 12 July 2018 to Question 162133 on Hospices: Children, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of funding for the Children’s Hospice Grant; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ellie Reeves","Lewisham West and Penge","Ellie Reeves","164516"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942544","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-19","<p>NHS Digital has advised that requests for data received by its Data Access Request Service for the period July 2017 to end June 2018 are as shown in the following table. These include time where the application is with the customer to provide additional detail, as well as the time that the application is with NHS Digital.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Mean</p></td><td><p>Median</p></td><td><p>Mode</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>92 working days</p></td><td><p>53 working days</p></td><td><p>9,16 or 34 working days</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: NHS Digital</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-07-19T13:12:52.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942544/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942544/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942544/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-16","NHS Digital","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what the (a) mean, (b) median and (c) modal time taken is for NHS Digital to process a request for data from universities and other healthcare research organisations.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Dan Poulter","164387"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942545","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-19","<p>NHS Digital has advised that it has data processor agreements in place with the UK Data Service so that archived survey datasets are made available to users registered with the UK Data Service under the Service’s safeguarded data terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><p>Anonymised data may be placed in the public domain while pseudonymised data is released with appropriate controls in place through a data sharing agreement. Requests for online access or extracts of data held by NHS Digital are strictly controlled by the Data Access Request Service. This ensures that data are only shared where there is an appropriate legal basis, a purpose that benefits the health and social care system, and that appropriate security safeguards are in place.</p><p> </p><p>The majority of NHS Digital survey datasets are disclosure controlled and then archived and made available for further research on the UK Data Service under end user licenses. Minimal NHS Digital resource is utilised to process applications for access to these archived survey datasets as they are managed in full by the UK Data Service.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","164390","2018-07-19T13:10:34.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942545/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942545/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942545/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-16","NHS Digital","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what NHS Digital does to ensure that requests for access to survey data are treated differently from requests to access patient and service use data.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Dan Poulter","164388"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942546","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-07-24","<p>No personal presentations from bidders were requested or received.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-07-24T08:53:34.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942546/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942546/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942546/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-07-16","HM Courts and Tribunals Service: Enforcement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether his Department (a) requested and (b) received presentations in person from bidders for the tender for Approved Enforcement Agency services, and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","164351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942547","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-07-24","<p>No site visits were made to the bidders during the procurement process.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-07-24T08:52:53.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942547/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942547/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942547/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-07-16","HM Courts and Tribunals Service: Enforcement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether his Department has made site visits to the bidders for the tender for Approved Enforcement Agency services; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","164352"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942548","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-19","<p>NHS Digital has advised that, as of 17 July 2018, 20 requests for Alternative Provider Medical Services data had been submitted to NHS Digital and accepted into the Data Access Request Service. Of these, two applications were not being progressed by the customer. Progress on the other requests is shown in the following table.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Less than three months after submission</p></td><td><p>More than three months after submission</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>In progress</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Approved</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>This period includes the change in legislative basis for the release of such data, specifically the introduction of the Data Protection Act 2018.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-07-19T13:08:38.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942548/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942548/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942548/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-16","Mental Illness: Surveys","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what proportion of applications to use APMS 2014 data received a decision more than three months after being submitted in the last period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Dan Poulter","164389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942549","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-19","<p>NHS Digital has advised that it has data processor agreements in place with the UK Data Service so that archived survey datasets are made available to users registered with the UK Data Service under the Service’s safeguarded data terms and conditions.</p><p> </p><p>Anonymised data may be placed in the public domain while pseudonymised data is released with appropriate controls in place through a data sharing agreement. Requests for online access or extracts of data held by NHS Digital are strictly controlled by the Data Access Request Service. This ensures that data are only shared where there is an appropriate legal basis, a purpose that benefits the health and social care system, and that appropriate security safeguards are in place.</p><p> </p><p>The majority of NHS Digital survey datasets are disclosure controlled and then archived and made available for further research on the UK Data Service under end user licenses. Minimal NHS Digital resource is utilised to process applications for access to these archived survey datasets as they are managed in full by the UK Data Service.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","164388","2018-07-19T13:10:34.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942549/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942549/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942549/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-16","NHS Digital","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how much resource NHS Digital is using to process applications by researchers to access survey data.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Dan Poulter","164390"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942550","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-07-19","<p>Our most recent data on unpaid maternity leave is from the Maternity and Paternity Rights Survey in 2009, which found that 11% of mothers received neither statutory maternity pay, occupational maternity pay nor Maternity Allowance. The main reasons for not receiving pay include not having sufficient continuous service with the same employer and being unemployed.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will shortly commission a new survey, which will provide updated information.</p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-07-19T16:29:44.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942550/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942550/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942550/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-07-16","Maternity Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what estimate he has made of the number of women who took unpaid maternity leave in 2017.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","164310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942551","Home Office","false","2018-07-23","<p>Published data on visa processing times, including the percentage of visas processed within published service standards, is published online at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data</a> (then listed by publication date under ‘UK Visas &amp; Immigration’).</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","164274","2018-07-23T17:33:54.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942551/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942551/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942551/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-16","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many immigration cases are outstanding for his Department that have not been resolved within the target time.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","164273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942552","Home Office","false","2018-07-23","<p>Published data on visa processing times, including the percentage of visas processed within published service standards, is published online at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data</a> (then listed by publication date under ‘UK Visas &amp; Immigration’).</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","164273","2018-07-23T17:33:54.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942552/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942552/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942552/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-16","Visas: Applications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many applicants have waited for over a year for their visas applications to be resolved in each year for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","164274"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942553","Department for Education","false","2018-07-24","<p>Membership of the national leadership board has yet to be determined. We will ensure that the board takes on board the views of those with expertise in speech, language and communication needs.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-07-24T14:41:53.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942553/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942553/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942553/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-07-16","Residential Care Leadership Board","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the Government response to the  review of the experiences and outcomes of children in residential special schools and colleges, published in November 2017, what plans he has to ensure that the national leadership board will include people with expertise in speech, language and communication needs.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Pow","Taunton Deane","Rebecca Pow","164496"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942554","Department for Transport","false","2018-07-20","<p>The Crossrail 2 project is still in the early design stages and no final decisions have been made on a route, funding, or financing.</p><p> </p><p>We have commissioned the Crossrail 2 Independent Affordability Review to examine ways to make the project more affordable. This review is progressing well, and when we receive its conclusions in the summer, we will discuss these with the Mayor of London and decide on next steps to progress the project.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-07-20T11:09:00.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942554/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942554/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942554/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-07-16","Crossrail 2 Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent progress has been made on Crossrail 2; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","164500"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942555","Department for Transport","false","2018-07-20","<p>The Secretary of State and other ministers have regular discussions with stakeholders, including the Mayor of London and Deputy Mayor for Transport, about the development of proposals for Crossrail 2. The current priority for the project is to improve its affordability, through the Independent Affordability Review.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-07-20T10:51:19.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942555/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942555/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942555/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-07-16","Crossrail 2 Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions he has had with (a) the Mayor of London and (b) Deputy Mayor for Transport on the construction of Crossrail 2.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","164501"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942556","Department for Transport","false","2018-07-20","<p>We have commissioned the Crossrail 2 Independent Affordability Review to ensure that the scheme delivers value for money. The Crossrail 2 cost estimates are under constant review by Transport for London and the Department for Transport to ensure that the scheme reflects the best evidence and learns from other infrastructure projects.</p><p> </p><p>As part of the Crossrail 2 Independent Affordability Review there is a focus on the cost of the project which includes an assessment of value engineering opportunities.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-07-20T09:41:07.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942556/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942556/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942556/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-07-16","Crossrail 2 Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the quantum of change in Crossrail 2 costings since the Crossrail Update report of May 2018.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","164502"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942557","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-07-24","<p>The Secretary of State has had no discussions with representatives of Corruption Watch to date, but officials from his Department recently met with the organisation to discuss restrictions to public reporting on court cases following the launch of a Corruption Watch UK report on the matter on 13 July.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-07-24T16:43:58.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942557/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942557/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942557/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-07-16","Courts: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether (a) he and (b) officials in his Department have had discussions with representatives of Corruption Watch UK on restrictions to public reporting on court cases.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","164503"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942558","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-19","<p>The Assuring Transformation (AT) data collection relates to patients with a diagnosis of learning disabilities and/or autistic spectrum disorder.</p><p> </p><p>The following table contains data taken from our most recent AT publication using May 2018 data, and covers patients who have an open hospital spell at the end of May 2018. The patients do not necessarily have a diagnosis of autism but have answered a question that describes the patient’s condition as autism. The patient’s total length of stay is over two years. This is then split by national ethnic category.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>May 2018</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total inpatients described to have autism, with a total length of stay over two years</p></td><td><p>260</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Ethnicity</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>White</p></td><td><p>210</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>British</p></td><td><p>205</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Irish</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Any other White background</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mixed</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>White and Black Caribbean</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>White and Black African</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>White and Asian</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Any other mixed background</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Asian or Asian British</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Indian</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Pakistani</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Bangladeshi</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Any other Asian background</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Black or Black British</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Caribbean</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>African</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Any other Black background</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Other Ethnic Groups</p></td><td><p>15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Chinese</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Any other ethnic group</p></td><td><p>*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Not Stated</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Not known</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: Assuring Transformation Collection, NHS Digital</p><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p> </p><p>The Assuring Transformation collection covers England, but includes patients whose care is commissioned in England and provided elsewhere in the United Kingdom. These figures represent the number of patients who are receiving inpatient care at the end of the month. Data in this table has been updated to include the most up-to-date figures so includes late submissions from commissioners.</p><p> </p><p>Numbers less than five have been replaced by '*' and other values have been rounded to the nearest five to minimise disclosure risks associated with small numbers. It should be noted that rows will therefore not always add up to the total.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-07-19T11:33:19.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942558/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942558/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942558/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-16","Autism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many people who have a diagnosis of autism have been in hospital for more than two years by ethnicity.","false","Biography information for Helen Hayes","Dulwich and West Norwood","Helen Hayes","164490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942559","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-19","<p>Data is not collected centrally on how many people have had instances of misdiagnosis or correction of diagnosis relating to autism.</p><p> </p><p>Data is not collected centrally on how many people have a co-morbid or other mental illnesses, prior or after receiving a diagnosis of autism.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","164492 ; 164493","2018-07-19T11:44:29.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942559/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942559/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942559/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-16","Autism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many instances of misdiagnosis which were corrected to a diagnosis of autism have occurred in each of the last five years by gender.","false","Biography information for Helen Hayes","Dulwich and West Norwood","Helen Hayes","164491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942560","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-08-07","<p>In accordance with the principle of open justice, the general rule is that all court proceedings must be held in open court to which the public and the media have access. There are, however, circumstances in which there may be restrictions on what can be reported. The statutory criteria for reporting restrictions in all criminal cases, including economic crime, can be automatic or discretionary.</p><p>Automatic restrictions are only applied in limited situations or to specific points in the journey of a case, for example in pre-trial hearings to prevent reporting of decisions on admissibility of evidence. If discretionary restrictions are applied, the court must first be satisfied that failure to apply these restrictions would render the administration of justice impractical. In either case, the media should be given an opportunity to make representations on the imposition of any reporting restriction and the courts have the power to lift or vary the restrictions if requested.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-08-07T09:32:43.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942560/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942560/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942560/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-07-16","Fraud: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the criteria are for the imposition of restrictions on media reporting applied to cases of economic crime.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","164504"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942561","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-19","<p>Data is not collected centrally on how many people have had instances of misdiagnosis or correction of diagnosis relating to autism.</p><p> </p><p>Data is not collected centrally on how many people have a co-morbid or other mental illnesses, prior or after receiving a diagnosis of autism.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","164491 ; 164493","2018-07-19T11:44:29.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942561/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942561/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942561/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-16","Autism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many instances of misdiagnosis were corrected to a diagnosis of autism in each ethnic group, in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Helen Hayes","Dulwich and West Norwood","Helen Hayes","164492"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942562","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-07-24","<p>Of the thirteen foreign bribery cases which have had a court hearing in the last 12 months, seven have been subject to reporting restrictions.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-07-24T16:44:59.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942562/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942562/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942562/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-07-16","Corruption: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many and what proportion of foreign bribery cases have been subject to reporting restrictions in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","164505"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942563","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-07-23","<p>A cross-whitehall official led meeting was convened on 28 June 2018 to discuss the ticketmaster incident. Attendees included representatives from the Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, the National Crime Agency and the National Cyber Security Centre.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-07-23T15:22:23.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942563/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942563/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942563/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-07-16","Ticketmaster: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 10 July 2018 to Question 160146 on Ticketmaster, what discussions his Department has had with the (a) National Crime Agency and (b) National Cyber Security Centre on Ticketmaster's recent data breach.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","164353"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942564","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-07-23","<p>The National Crime Agency’s criminal investigation is ongoing. The National Cyber Security Centre (NCSC) has concluded a number of investigative strands to help Ticketmaster remediate and mitigate the compromise, and have since released relevant advice and guidance to the NCSC website: <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/news/statement-ticketmaster-cyber-incident" target="_blank">https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/news/statement-ticketmaster-cyber-incident</a></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-07-23T15:23:46.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942564/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942564/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942564/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-07-16","Ticketmaster: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 10 July 2018 to Question 160146 on Ticketmaster, what progress has been made on the investigation into Ticketmaster's recent data breach.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","164354"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942565","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-07-23","<p>Ticketmaster have released details about the data incident which stated that 5% of its global customer base had been affected and those affected have been contacted by the company with details on how to reset passwords. The National Cyber Security Centre (NCSC) has issued advice to customers of Ticketmaster which includes guidance on changing passwords which is freely available on the NCSC website. The Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) is in regular contact with Ticketmaster, and their investigation into this matter is ongoing. The ICO will provide further detail on the incident on conclusion of their investigation.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-07-23T15:24:46.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942565/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942565/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942565/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-07-16","Ticketmaster: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to Answer of 10 July 2018 to Question 160146 on Ticketmaster, how many consumers were affected by Ticketmaster's recent data breach.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","164355"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942566","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-19","<p>Data is not collected centrally on how many people have had instances of misdiagnosis or correction of diagnosis relating to autism.</p><p> </p><p>Data is not collected centrally on how many people have a co-morbid or other mental illnesses, prior or after receiving a diagnosis of autism.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","164491 ; 164492","2018-07-19T11:44:29.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942566/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942566/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942566/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-16","Autism: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many autistic females under the age of 18 have been diagnosed (a) with co-morbid mental illness and (b) with a mental illness prior to their autism diagnosis.","false","Biography information for Helen Hayes","Dulwich and West Norwood","Helen Hayes","164493"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942567","Home Office","false","2018-08-29","<p>I am not aware of any reporting restrictions in relation to the three current unexplained wealth orders.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2018-08-29T15:27:05.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942567/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942567/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942567/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-16","Unexplained Wealth Orders: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate he has made of the proportion of cases involving unexplained wealth orders that have had reporting restrictions applied to them.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","164506"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942568","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-24","<p>There are no current plans for the Department to classify obesity as a disease.</p><p> </p><p>We will be launching the seven consultations announced in ‘Childhood obesity: a plan for action, chapter 2’ before the end of 2018. We will consider all responses to the consultations before setting out the next steps.</p><p> </p><p>‘Childhood obesity: a plan for action, chapter 2’ is available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/childhood-obesity-a-plan-for-action-chapter-2" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/childhood-obesity-a-plan-for-action-chapter-2</a></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","164438","2018-07-24T15:09:11.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942568/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942568/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942568/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-16","Obesity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, if he will support the research into whether obesity should be classified as a disease including the possible consequences of such a classification on NHS commissioning and other services.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","164437"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942569","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-07-24","<p>HM Prison and Probation Service publishes a breakdown of all population and capacity figures by prison at the end of every month which are accessible at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/prison-population-figures-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/prison-population-figures-2018</a> with the most recent available being for June 2018.</p><p> </p><p>The following table identifies all open prisons in the adult male prison estate with their respective operational capacity, population and occupancy as at Friday 29 June 2018.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Prison Name</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Operational Capacity</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Population</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Occupancy</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Blantyre House</p></td><td colspan="3"><p>Prison not currently in use</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Ford</p></td><td><p>544</p></td><td><p>535</p></td><td><p>98.35%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Hatfield</p></td><td><p>378</p></td><td><p>374</p></td><td><p>98.94%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Hewell Grange*</p></td><td><p>224</p></td><td><p>221</p></td><td><p>98.66%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Hollesley Bay</p></td><td><p>480</p></td><td><p>466</p></td><td><p>97.08%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Kirkham</p></td><td><p>653</p></td><td><p>586</p></td><td><p>89.74%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Kirklevington Grange</p></td><td><p>283</p></td><td><p>265</p></td><td><p>93.64%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Leyhill</p></td><td><p>515</p></td><td><p>513</p></td><td><p>99.61%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North Sea Camp</p></td><td><p>420</p></td><td><p>408</p></td><td><p>97.14%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Prescoed</p></td><td><p>260</p></td><td><p>253</p></td><td><p>97.31%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Spring Hill</p></td><td><p>326</p></td><td><p>320</p></td><td><p>98.31%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Standford Hill</p></td><td><p>464</p></td><td><p>461</p></td><td><p>9