"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942585","Cabinet Office","false","2018-07-18","<p>The team’s remit is to fulfil the recommendations of the relevant strand of the National Security Capability Review.</p><p> </p><p>The review can be found online here:</p><p><a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/705347/6.4391_CO_National-Security-Review_web.pdf" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/705347/6.4391_CO_National-Security-Review_web.pdf</a></p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2018-07-18T11:18:31.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942585/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942585/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942585/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-07-16","National Security Communications Unit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the purpose and remit are of the National Security Communications Team.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","164286"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942586","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-07-26","<p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy spent a combined total of £3.5m on services from the accountancy firms Deloitte, Ernst &amp; Young, KPMG and Pricewaterhouse Coopers in the last twelve months, from July 2017 to June 2018.</p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-07-26T12:02:25.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942586/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942586/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942586/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-07-16","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Accountancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how much his Department has spent with the Big Four accountancy firms in the last twelve months.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","164287"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942587","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-07-25","<p>The Department has incurred the following amounts with the ‘Big Four’ accounting firms in the twelve months to 30 June 2018:</p><p> </p><p>KPMG £361,730.38 (VAT included)</p><p>Deloitte £0</p><p>PricewaterhouseCoopers £0</p><p>Ernst &amp; Young £0</p>","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris",,"2018-07-25T15:55:28.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942587/answer","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942587/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942587/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-07-16","Department for Exiting the European Union: Accountancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how much his Department has spent with the Big Four accountancy firms in the last twelve months.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","164288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942588","Department for Education","false","2018-07-24","<p>The Department for Education does not hold the information in the requested format.</p><p>Figures on children in need are published at a local authority level, not a constituency level. Therefore, the figures for Lewisham Deptford constituency are not available.</p><p>The number of children referred to social services on one or more occasions within the same reporting year is not a figure that is routinely produced. Similarly, the number of children referred to social services at least once within consecutive reporting years is also not routinely produced.</p><p>The department publishes figures on the number of referrals which were within 12 months of a previous referral. This is a measure of the number of re-referrals rather than the number of children re-referred. Last year, the number of children to which these referrals applied was published for the first time. However, this information is not available for earlier years. These figures have been provided below.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Table </strong><strong>1</strong><strong>: Number of referrals to children's social services that were within 12 months of a previous referral from 2012-13 to 2016-17, and number of children who had a referral within 12 months of a previous referral in 2016-17</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Re-Referrals</strong></p></td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>England</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>147,700</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>154,000</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>152,400</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>138,700</p></td><td><p>141,560</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Lewisham</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>414</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>262</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>377</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>387</p></td><td><p>334</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><p><strong>Children Re-referred</strong></p></td><td colspan="2"><p> </p></td><td colspan="2"><p> </p></td><td colspan="2"><p> </p></td><td colspan="2"><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>England</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>..</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>..</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>..</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>..</p></td><td><p>117,710</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Lewisham</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>..</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>..</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>..</p></td><td colspan="2"><p>..</p></td><td><p>319</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The total number of referrals to children’s social services within one reporting year is also reported in table C1 of main tables in the ‘children in need and child protection’ statistical collection on GOV.UK. It can be accessed at this link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-children-in-need" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-children-in-need</a>.</p><p>These figures do not include the number of children who are referred in consecutive years however, as this measure is not routinely produced.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","164480","2018-07-24T14:47:13.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942588/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942588/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942588/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-07-16","Children: Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many children in (a) Lewisham Deptford constituency, (b) Lewisham borough and (c) England  were referred to children's social services on more than one occasion in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","164479"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942589","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-07-23","<p>The Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government has spent the following amounts in the last 12 months (to 30 June 2018):</p><p> </p><p>KPMG - £192,275</p><p>Deloitte - £73,962</p><p>PWC – nil</p><p>Ernst &amp; Young – nil</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-07-23T16:04:39.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942589/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942589/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942589/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-07-16","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Accountancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how much his Department has spent with the Big Four accountancy firms in the last twelve months.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","164289"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942590","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-07-23","<p>Northern Ireland Office officials are in regular contact with Department of Health Northern Ireland officials to ensure that, following a recommendation from the expert panel, appropriate licences are in place which allow patients to be treated with cannabis-based medicines.</p><p>It would not be appropriate for me to discuss the specific circumstances of certain individuals.</p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2018-07-23T08:49:05.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942590/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942590/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942590/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-07-16","Cannabis: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussion she has had with the Department of Health in Northern Ireland the conditions of the licence for Billy Caldwell to ensure the availability of medicinal cannabis without the need to travel to Belfast.","false","Biography information for Tonia Antoniazzi","Gower","Tonia Antoniazzi","164518"
