"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942620","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-07-23","<p>We committed to look at concerns about rules of the statutory Criminal Injuries Compensation Scheme as part of the Department’s work to develop a strategy for victims. The strategy will be published this summer.</p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar","165653","2018-07-23T14:16:22.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942620/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942620/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942620/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-07-16","Criminal Injuries Compensation Authority","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what plans he has to review the rules governing the Criminal Injuries Compensation Authority; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","164485"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942621","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-07-19","<p>As set out in the 2016 Prison Safety Reform White Paper and 2017 manifesto, we remain committed to building up to 10,000 modern and decent prison places to replace old, expensive and unsuitable accommodation. We intend to build the first prison at Wellingborough through public capital, with construction work expected to begin late 2018 / early 2019 with completion projected for early 2021.</p><p>The Department awarded to Kier Construction Limited a two-stage contract to design and construct the prison at Wellingborough on 19 February 2018. Negotiations are underway with the constructor on delivery of the cost of the new prison and this is also subject to the usual value for money assessments. The prison has been designed to provide largely single cell accommodation.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","164481 ; 164482 ; 164483 ; 164484","2018-07-19T12:58:51.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942621/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942621/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942621/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-07-16","Prison Accommodation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what requirements his Department plans to place on the design and building of new prisons relating to the number of occupants in each room.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","164486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942622","Cabinet Office","false","2019-05-15","<p>The Bank of England does not own any gold reserves of its own, except for two bars held for display at the Bank of England Museum. However, the Bank provides safe custody for the UK's gold reserves and for other customers. It has only started recently publishing the weight of all the gold in its custody on its website, which includes data back to 2011. On 30 June 2018, it held 166,516,000 fine troy ounces of gold. There is no equivalent data available for 1998 and 2008.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2019-05-15T17:33:50.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942622/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942622/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942622/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-07-16","Gold and Foreign Exchange Reserves","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the gold reserves of the Bank of England were on 30 June (a) 1998, (b) 2008 and (c) 2018.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Lefroy","Stafford","Jeremy Lefroy","164422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942623","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-07-23","<p>Implementation of the Birds and Habitats Directives in the UK is devolved. In England, the Directives are implemented through the Wildlife and Countryside Act 1981, the Conservation of Habitats and Species Regulations 2017 and the Conservation of Offshore Marine Habitats and Species Regulations 2017.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-07-23T15:13:26.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942623/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942623/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942623/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-07-16","Nature Conservation: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what plans he has to implement the Birds and Habitats Directive in the UK.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","164403"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942624","Treasury","false","2018-07-19","<p>It is not possible to produce meaningful estimates of the amount of levy payments made by employers in specific geographical areas. HMRC have information on where PAYE schemes are registered, though not on the workplaces of the employer. Many large employers will have various workplaces across the UK or outsource their payroll to a payroll provider based in a different location.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-07-19T14:29:40.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942624/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942624/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942624/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-07-16","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many employers in (a) Ashfield constituency, (b) Nottingham South, and (c) Nottinghamshire pay the apprenticeship levy.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","164382"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942625","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-07-24","<p>The government is preparing a Statutory Instrument that will implement the EU Invasive Species Regulation in the UK.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-07-24T10:22:20.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942625/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942625/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942625/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-07-16","Non-native Species: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will make it his policy to replicate the EU Alien Species Regulation after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","164404"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942626","Department for Education","false","2018-07-19","<p>Apprenticeship achievement rates are published in our annual national achievement rates tables by local authority district. Tables for the 2016 to 2017 academic year are published here.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/national-achievement-rates-tables-2016-to-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/national-achievement-rates-tables-2016-to-2017</a>.</p><p>The table attached provides the cohort numbers and proportions achieving the advanced Level 3 apprenticeship for Ashfield constituency, Nottinghamshire, Nottingham local authority district and England for the 2016 to 2017 academic year and show that Ashfield outperform the local area and the country. Figures are based on learner home postcode. We do not hold data for the United Kingdom, but for England only.</p><p>The apprenticeship levy was introduced in April 2017. We do not hold the information on apprenticeship employers that pay/do not pay the levy, but do hold information on apprenticeship service (AS) accounts that hold levy funds, which can be used to fund an apprenticeship. Apprenticeship starts (including those that are levy supported) in the Ashfield constituency are shown in the attached table.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","164384","2018-07-19T13:54:05.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942626/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942626/answer","Proportion_achieving_Level_3_and_apprenticeship_starts_in_Ashfield.doc","Proportion_achieving_Level_3_and_apprenticeship_starts_in_Ashfield.doc","Proportion_achieving_Level_3_and_Ashfield_starts","Proportion_achieving_Level_3_and_Ashfield_starts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942626/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-07-16","Apprentices: Qualifications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many and what proportion of apprenticeships in (a) Ashfield constituency, (b) Nottinghamshire and (c) the UK achieve NVQ level 3.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","164383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942627","Department for Education","false","2018-07-19","<p>Apprenticeship achievement rates are published in our annual national achievement rates tables by local authority district. Tables for the 2016 to 2017 academic year are published here.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/national-achievement-rates-tables-2016-to-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/national-achievement-rates-tables-2016-to-2017</a>.</p><p>The table attached provides the cohort numbers and proportions achieving the advanced Level 3 apprenticeship for Ashfield constituency, Nottinghamshire, Nottingham local authority district and England for the 2016 to 2017 academic year and show that Ashfield outperform the local area and the country. Figures are based on learner home postcode. We do not hold data for the United Kingdom, but for England only.</p><p>The apprenticeship levy was introduced in April 2017. We do not hold the information on apprenticeship employers that pay/do not pay the levy, but do hold information on apprenticeship service (AS) accounts that hold levy funds, which can be used to fund an apprenticeship. Apprenticeship starts (including those that are levy supported) in the Ashfield constituency are shown in the attached table.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","164383","2018-07-19T13:54:05.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942627/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942627/answer","Proportion_achieving_Level_3_and_apprenticeship_starts_in_Ashfield.doc","Proportion_achieving_Level_3_and_apprenticeship_starts_in_Ashfield.doc","Proportion_achieving_Level_3_and_Ashfield_starts","Proportion_achieving_Level_3_and_Ashfield_starts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942627/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-07-16","Apprentices: Ashfield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many people in Ashfield co